This package contains the scripts required by the _tupitu.be extension_ for
Inkscape. This extension allows you to post and share your works in the 
tupitu.be website directly from the Inkscape interface.

Note: If you haven't installed Inkscape already, you can download it 
      from: http://inkscape.org/download/

Now, how do I install this extension in my computer?

LINUX

- Download the file tupitube-inkscape.zip from http://www.tupitu.be/downloads
- Uncompress the zip file and get in the directory tupitube-inkscape
- Copy the files tupitube.inx and tupitube.py within your user home, 
  specifically into the directory:
  ".config/inkscape/extensions"
- Run Inkscape from the Programs menu and draw anything you want to share
- When you are done, go to Extensions -> Tupitu.be and fill the form
- Press "Apply" and your work will be available from http://tupitu.be

MAC OSX

- Download the file tupitube-inkscape.zip from http://www.tupitu.be/downloads
- Uncompress the zip file and get in the directory tupitube-inkscape
- Copy the files tupitube.inx and tupitube.py into the directory:
  "/Applications/Inkscape.app/Contents/Resources/extensions"
- Run Inkscape from the Programs menu and draw anything you want to share
- When you are done, go to Extensions -> Tupitu.be and fill the form
- Press "Apply" and your work will be available from http://tupitu.be

WINDOWS

- Download the file tupitube-inkscape.zip from http://www.tupitu.be/downloads 
- Uncompress the zip file and get in the directory tupitube-inkscape 
- Copy the files tupitube.inx and tupitube.py into the directory:
  "C:\Program Files\Inkscape\share\extensions"
- Run Inkscape from the Programs menu and draw anything you want to share 
- When you are done, go to Extensions -> Tupitu.be and fill the form
- Press "Apply" and your work will be available from http://tupitu.be 

Note: Remember to restart Inkscape to get this plugin available from the 
      extensions menu. 
